Plague, bubonic - Zambia 20010315.0525
Date: Mon 26 Mar 2001 11:27:37 -0500
From: Marianne Hopp <mhopp@iri.ldgo.columbia.edu>
Source: WHO Disease Outbreaks, 26 Mar 2001 [edited
<http://www.who.int/disease-outbreak-news/n2001/march/26march2001.html>

The World Health Organization has received preliminary reports of 23 cases
admitted to hospital, including 3 deaths, in Petauke district, Eastern
Province. The last case reported was 15 Mar 2001. Measures have been taken
to intensify surveillance, strengthen control and management of the
disease, and provide health education messages on its prevention.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[It appears that this outbreak may now be under control. - Mod.ES
